article.description: Eshaya Murphy and Meghan Gnekow scored 15 points each to lead Southern California to a 66-45 victory over No. 25 Arizona State.
article.headline: USC's Murphy, Gnekow combine for 30 points
article.linkText: USC holds off late rally from No. 25 Sun Devils
article.story:
LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Eshaya Murphy and Meghan Gnekow scored 15 points each to lead Southern California to a 66-45 victory over No. 25 Arizona State on Sunday.

Gnekow also led with nine rebounds.

The Trojans (12-4) forced 21 turnovers and collected 11 steals.

Gnekow's 3-pointer eight minutes into the first half gave USC an 8-6 lead they never relinquished.

Trailing by as much as 10 points, Arizona State (11-5) rallied to with 23-20 with 3:40 left in the first half.

USC answered with a 9-1 run of their own, including a last-second jumper by forward Jamie Funn to enter halftime ahead, 32-21.

Funn finished with 12 points and guard Brynn Cameron had 11.

Amy Denson led Arizona State's scoring with eight points.
